        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Callback to be called when a zero-crossing event is detected.</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>When using MycilaPulseAnalyzer library, this callback can be registered like this:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>pulseAnalyzer.onZeroCross(Mycila::ThyristorDimmer::onZeroCross);</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>When using your own ISR with the RobotDyn ZCD, you can call this method with delayUntilZero == 200 since the length of the ZCD pulse is about 400 us.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>When using your own ISR with the ZCd from Daniel S, you can call this method with delayUntilZero == 550 since the length of the ZCD pulse is about 1100 us. </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
